<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangxi Progresses in Resolving Civilian Disputes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1602132194 Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1602132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jiangxi has achieved dramatic results in resolving 
civilian conflicts and armed disputes. Last year 35 civilian 
conflicts and armed disputes took place, leaving eight dead and 
causing direct economic losses of 140,000 yuan, a decrease of 
respectively 66 percent, 62 percent, and 79 percent as compared 
with the previous year. In preventing civilian conflicts and 
armed disputes, all levels of the departments were firm in 
implementing the central and provincial arrangements, were quick 
to act, and were efficient in their measures. 
  Early last year, the provincial government signed agreements 
with the relevant prefectural, city, and provincial departments 
on preventing and mediating civilian conflicts and armed 
disputes. They organized personnel to mediate and resolve 29 
cases of civilian conflicts. Ganzhou, Jian, and Jingdezhen 
authorities conducted a no-armed-dispute campaign this year, and 
they were successful. 

</TEXT>

