<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mainland Airplane Hijacked En Route to Fuzhou </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1802040694 Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News 
Network in Mandarin 0320 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1802040694 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei China Broadcasting Corporation News 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] A Boeing-737 airplane from Mainland China's 
Southwest Airlines was hijacked while en route from Changsha to 
Fuzhou this morning, and landed at Chiang Kai-shek Airport at 
1042 [0242 GMT]. It was the 11th Communist Chinese airliner 
hijacked to Taiwan since 6 April last year. 
  According to sources, there were 120 passengers and eight 
crew members on the Boeing-737 airliner bearing the serial 
number B-2599. At 1018, aviation control units from our Air 
Force spotted the airliner deviating from its route. The Tainan 
Air Base sent two F-5E fighters to guide the airliner to land. 
The authorities have instructed through proper channels that 
the matter be handled in accordance with the established 
principles. 
  Since the ninth Communist Chinese airliner was hijacked to 
Taiwan late last year, the government has lowered the level at 
which it will comment on airplane hijackings. 

</TEXT>

