<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina </TI></H3>
<H4>   Bosnian Premier To Visit U.S. </H4>
<F P=102> OW2102053494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0516 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2102053494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, February 20 (XINHUA) -- Prime Minister 
Haris Silajdzic of Bosnia-Herzegovina will arrive here Monday 
[21 February] for talks with U.S. Government and Congress 
officials. 
  The visit comes only one day after the expiry of a NATO 
ultimatum for the Bosnian Serbs to withdraw or put under UN 
control all their heavy weapons in Sarajevo, or face NATO air 
strikes, which were deemed as unnecessary by NATO and UN 
officials "for the time being." 
  Accompanying Silajdzic will be Bosnian Parliament President 
Miro Lazovic and Presidency Member Ivo Komsic. 
  "The visit comes at a crucial moment for the future of the 
Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina and its people," the local 
Bosnian Embassy said. 
  Washington has been sympathetic with the Bosnian Government, 
which is comprised mainly of Muslims, the grieved side in the 
22- month war in the Yugoslav republic. 
  Appearing in an interview of the ABC Television, U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher said, "finding a rational 
settlement, finding one that is satisfactory to the Muslims, has 
to be a very high priority." 
  Christopher, who is scheduled to meet Silajdzic Monday 
morning, said Washington is trying to know what the Bosnian 
Muslims' "reasonable requirements" are and help them achieve 
them. 
  Silajdzic will stay in Washington for three days. He will 
first meet Deputy Secretary of State Peter Tarnoff and Assistant 
Secretary of State Stephen Oxman Monday morning. 
  The prime minister will have a second meeting with 
Christopher Thursday afternoon. 
  After their stay in Washington, Silajdzic and his entourage 
will go to New York Friday, the Bosnian Embassy said. 

</TEXT>

