<H3> <TI>   China, Russia, CIS States Conclude Border Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202101794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0958 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2202101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 22 (XINHUA) -- The 12th round of 
talks between the working group of the Chinese Government 
delegation on border issues and the working group of the joint 
delegation on border issues of Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, the 
Russian Federation and Tajikistan was held here from February 15 
to 22. 
  In a serious and realistic atmosphere, they discussed and 
made some progress on the border issues between China and the 
above-mentioned four countries. 
  The two sides decided that the next round of talks will be 
held in Bishkek. 
  During the talks, Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Dai Bingguo 
met with the working group of the joint delegation headed by 
Afanasyev. 

