<H3> <TI>   Shandong Governor Meets With Ukrainian Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2202044094 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2202044094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A seven-member government delegation from the 
Kherson Oblast of the Republic of Ukraine headed by (Valinikov 
Aleksandr Gikhonovich), head of the oblast, paid a friendly 
visit to our province recently. The major purpose of the visit 
was to explore the possibility for the province and the oblast 
to establish friendly ties. 
  Provincial Governor Zhao Zhihao cordially met with the 
delegation at the provincial government office on the afternoon 
of 21 February. He extended a welcome to the delegation, saying: 
Shandong and Kherson have achieved substantial results in their 
economic and trade cooperation over the past few years. They 
have also proved highly capable of mutual economic cooperation 
and have displayed the tremendous potential and bright prospects 
for strengthening cooperation and exchanges. It is hoped that 
both sides will conduct further exchanges and cooperation in 
more fields in the future. 
  During the meeting, Zhao Zhihao, governor of Shandong, and 
(Gikhonovich), head of Kherson Oblast, signed an agreement on 
the exchanges and cooperation between Shandong Province and 
Kherson Oblast. 
  Provincial Vice Governor Song Fatang also held a working 
discussion with the delegation on the same day. 

</TEXT>

