<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   Provincial TV Officials, U.S. Broadcasting Figures Meet </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2002090594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0828 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2002090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 20 (XINHUA) -- A senior TV 
delegation from the United States, headed by Managing Director 
of the United States-China Chamber of Commerce Bruno Z. Wu, and 
representatives from China's 10 provincial TV stations met here 
today to discuss how to promote exchanges between them. 
  Representatives from another 20 provincial TV stations will 
start discussions with the U.S. delegation Tuesday [22 February]. 
  At the meeting this morning, B. Z. Wu, also president of the 
China International Partnership Advertising Agency (CIPAA), said 
that China's economic development has attracted world attention. 
  Jonathan Jephcott, director in charge of business 
development 
in Asia and the Pacific region of the A.C. Nielsen [firm], said 
that his company is ready to carry out cooperation with its 
Chinese counterparts, to help upgrade China's advertising 
business in line with international practices. 
  Representatives from the Metro Goldwyn Mayer (MGM) and the 
Jones International Ltd. expressed views on the exchange of TV 
programs and TV education. 

