<H3> <TI>   Bank of Tokyo Provides Scholarships for Beijing Institutes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1902095094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0857 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1902095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 19 (XINHUA) -- The Bank of Tokyo 
of Japan recently decided to provide 960,000 yen as scholarships 
for two institutes in Beijing. 
  This morning a ceremony was held for signing an agreement on 
the scholarship, attended by Beijing Mayor Li Qiyan and 
president of the Bank of Tokyo. 
  The two institutes are Beijing Institute of Economics and 
Beijing Institute of Finance and Trade. 
  The annual scholarship will be granted to 32 students from 
the two institutes. 
  Li Qiyan noted that this year marks the 15th anniversary of 
the establishment of sister relationship between Beijing and 
Tokyo. 
  He said that the scholarship set by the Bank of Tokyo will 
certainly promote the friendly relations between the two cities. 
  He also expressed welcome for the Bank of Tokyo to set up 
office in the Chinese capital. 

</TEXT>

