<H3> <TI>   DPRK Marks Anniversary of Cultural, Aviation Accords </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202061094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1350 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2202061094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Gao Haorong (7559 3185 2837)] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, 21 Feb (XINHUA) -- Korea's [DPRK] 
Committee for Cultural Relations With Foreign Countries and 
Civil Aviation Bureau hosted a banquet today to mark the 35th 
anniversary of the "Sino-Korean Agreement on Cultural 
Cooperation" and the "Sino-Korean Agreement on Air Transport." 
  Speaking at the banquet, Chong Chun-ki, chairman of Korea's 
Committee for Cultural Relations With Foreign Countries, said: 
The past 35 years have witnessed numerous cultural exchanges 
between Korea and China. These exchanges have contributed to 
socialist construction in both countries, greatly developed the 
civil aviation sectors of the two countries, and strengthened 
the bonds of friendship between the two countries. 
  Chong Chun-ki said: The Chinese people have scored 
tremendous success in its quest for social stability and 
socialism with their own characteristics. The Korean people are 
very glad about this, and would like to wish China smooth 
progress in all its undertakings. He expressed the belief that 
joint efforts by the two peoples would help constantly develop 
the traditional Korean-Chinese friendship. 
  Ning Fukui, Chinese charge d'affaires ad interim in Korea, 
attended the banquet. 
  The "Sino-Korean Agreement on Cultural Cooperation" and the 
"Sino-Korean Agreement on Air Transport" were signed on 21 and 
18 February 1959, respectively. 

</TEXT>

