<H3> <TI>   ROK To Provide $40 Million in Development Aid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2002091594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0902 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2002091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, February 20 (XINHUA) -- The Government of the 
Republic of Korea plans to provide 40 million U.S. dollars in an 
economic development cooperation fund (EDCF) to China this year, 
a government official said here today. 
  "We have decided to furnish 40 million U.S. dollars to China 
initially this year, taking into account the projects the money 
would finance and the availability of EDCF funds," the official 
said. 
  The projects include a bridge construction in north China's 
coastal city of Tianjin, harbor expansion in the eastern 
province of Shandong, and railroad facilities and airport 
communications and control facilities in northeastern province 
of Heilongjiang. 
  The official added that Seoul made the decision after a 
feasibility study of the projects by a fact-finding team sent to 
China toward the end of last year. 

</TEXT>

