<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Prime Minister Receives Chinese Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1702192194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1900 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1702192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, February 17 (XINHUA) -- Yemeni Prime Minister 
Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas received Chinese Ambassador to Yemen 
Li Liugen in Aden today. 
  XINHUA learned that the Yemeni prime minister and the 
Chinese 
ambassador discussed some issues related to economic cooperation 
between the two countries. 
  Al-'Attas also expressed his profound concern over the three 
kidnapped Chinese experts who were working on the Jahanna-Maareb 
Road construction project. 
  The three experts, who were kidnapped on February 12, 
include 
the head of a Chinese technical team executing the road building 
project, the chief engineer and the assistant manager of the 
project. 
  The security situation in Yemen has been deteriorating in 
the 
recent years, and there has been recurrent abductions of 
accredited foreign diplomats, foreign tourists and employees of 
foreign companies operating in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

