<H3> <TI>   PRC Officials Meets Italian Senate President </TI></H3>
<H4>   Qiao Shi Meets Senate Leader </H4>
<F P=102> OW1802141094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1347 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1802141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 18 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman 
of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's 
Congress (NPC), had a cordial talk here this evening with 
Giovanni Spatolini, president of the Italian Senate. 
  They agreed that in recent years, the all-round relations 
between China and Italy had been satisfactory. 
  Qiao said China is willing to continuously expand her 
economic cooperation with Italy and that China welcomes more 
Italian entrepreneurs to come and invest here. He also voiced 
the hope that the bilateral ties would gain further development 
on the existing basis. 
  Spatolini praised China for its role in maintaining world 
peace and said that many Italian entrepreneurs want to invest in 
China. 
  They expressed concern over the latest situation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and voiced the hope that the United Nations 
would help settle the conflict by peaceful means. 
  They also exchanged views on other regional and 
international 
issues of common interest. 
  Spatolini visited China nine years ago when he was the 
Italian defense minister. 
  Qiao today extended a warm welcome to Spatolini, saying that 
the visit would help enhance the mutual understanding and 
friendship between the two countries. 
  Wu Jieping, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, 
took 
part in the meeting. 
  Afterwards, Qiao hosted a dinner in honor of Spatolini, who 
arrived here this morning as guest of the NPC Standing Committee. 

</TEXT>

