<F P=103> OW1902131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 19 (XINHUA) -- Chinese 
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met with visiting 
Italian Senate President Giovanni Spatolini here this afternoon. 
  They exchanged views on bilateral relations and 
international 
issues of common concern. 
  Qian said that Sino-Italian ties are close, with frequent 
high- level contacts, adding that spatolini's current China 
visit would further promote the relations between the two 
countries. 
  Spatolini recalled his first China tour in 1985 when he was 
the italian defense minister, noting that great changes have 
taken place in Beijing since then. 
  Touching on religious issues, Qian said that China has 
recently promulgated two regulations on religion, pointing out 
that the purpose of this move "is to protect the normal 
religious activities instead of limiting them". 
  Earlier today, Spatolini delivered a speech at Beijing 
University, where he also received an honorary doctorate in 
history. 

