Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 21 (XINHUA) -- China's president, 
Jiang Zemin, met visiting Italian Senate President Giovanni 
Spatolini here this morning. 
  During the meeting at Zhongnanhai, headquarters of the 
Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and the State 
Council, Jiang expressed his satisfaction with the smooth 
development of Sino-Italian relations. 
  Jiang said that Sino-Italian ties are close, with frequent 
high- level contacts, adding that much progress has been made in 
bilateral cooperation in various fields including economy and 
trade. 
  The Chinese president also extended his appreciation for the 
positive efforts the Italian Government has made in pushing 
forward the full normalization of relations between the European 
Economic Community and China. 
  Spatolini said that Italy is very interested in China's 
economic development and Italian entrepreneurs have shown great 
confidence in investing in China. 
  He said that one of the purposes of his current visit was to 
promote cultural exchanges between the two countries. 
  Jiang said that cultural exchanges between China and Italy 
went back to ancient times and prospects for them were still 
promising. 
  During his stay in Beijing, Spatolini received an honorary 
doctorate in history from Beijing University. 
  Spatolini first visited China in 1985 when he was the 
Italian 
defense minister. 

