<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 21 (XINHUA) -- A Sino-Slovak 
economic and trade seminar was held this morning. Visiting 
Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar, and the chairman of the 
China Council for the Promotion of International Trade, Zheng 
Hongye, spoke at the closing ceremony at noon. 
  Zheng said that, economic and trade relations between China 
and Slovakia had witnessed rapid development. 
  He said that the seminar would no doubt contribute to the 
development of such relations. 
  He expressed the hope that business people of the two 
countries will strengthen exchanges and cooperation, so as to 
push forward the development of bilateral economic and trade 
relations. 
