<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Official Discusses Role of District Advisers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2102093294 Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO in Chinese 21 Feb 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> HK2102093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report: "XINHUA Official Discloses Namelist of Over 200 </F>
District Affairs Advisers To Be Announced Early Next Month"] 
  [Text] Zhang Xiting, director of the XINHUA Hong Kong 
Branch's office in the New Territories, disclosed that the New 
Territories will account for a certain proportion of the more 
than 200 district affairs advisers to be announced early next 
month. 
  After attending the opening ceremony of the Tsuen Wan Basic 
Law Promotion Carnival, held yesterday, Zhang Xiting was asked 
by reporters about the proportion of district advisers from the 
New Territories and Tsuen Wan in the namelist to be announced 
next month. 
  Zhang Xiting reiterated that the namelist will include 
figures from various strata and circles. The main task of the 
district advisers is to offer advice to the Chinese side on 
district affairs. 
  On the same occasion, Cheng Kai-nam, secretary of the 
Democratic Alliance for Betterment of Hong Kong, told reporters 
that the alliance will discuss at its central standing committee 
meeting tomorrow the question of its members being invited as 
district affairs advisers. 
  Cheng stressed that the duties of the district affairs 
advisers and third group of Hong Kong affairs advisers to be 
appointed next month should not involve administration of the 
current Hong Kong government, but they can offer advice to China 
on post-1997 affairs. 

</TEXT>

