<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   New XINHUA Macao Deputy Head Views Economic Development </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1902083194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0737 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1902083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, February 19 (XINHUA) -- Li Shuilin, 
newly-appointed deputy director of the XINHUA NEWS AGENCY Macao 
branch, said that he was determined to do a good job at his new 
post through hard work. 
  While meeting with reporters here today, Li said, friendly 
cooperation between the two Governments of China and Portugal 
and the rapid economic development on China's Mainland will 
create sound conditions for the economic development in Macao. 
  Li, who arrived here on February 16, was formerly director 
of 
the Asia and Africa Affairs Department of the Chinese Ministry 
of Foreign Economic Relations and Trade. 

</TEXT>

