<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deng Xiaoping Leaves Shanghai for Home 19 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2002052694 Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO in Chinese 20 Feb p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK2002052694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Deng Xiaoping Left Shanghai on 19 </F>
February"] 
  [Text] Shanghai, 19 Feb (WEN WEI PO)--Deng Xiaoping this 
morning boarded a special train leaving Shanghai. 
  The municipality's major party and government officials, Wu 
Bangguo and Huang Ju, saw Deng off at the railway station. 
  A source said Deng Xiaoping's special train was heading 
northward for Beijing, but he did not rule out the possibility 
that the train might go to other cities. 
  The schedules of all trains arriving and leaving the 
Shanghai 
station this morning were changed unexpectedly. Passengers were 
given the explanation that the change was due to the departure 
of a special train from Minhang, Shanghai, carrying a Long March 
rocket to the Xichang satellite launching base. 
  Deng Xiaoping has spent the Spring Festival in Shanghai in 
the past few years since 1988. He showed up in public on the 
Spring Festival this year, which has caused various speculations 
on his health. According to those who were present at the 
railway station seeing Deng Xiaoping off, he looked in pretty 
good shape [jing shen bu cuo 4737 4377 0008 6934] today. And 
Deng Xiaoping's being able to travel by train may be in itself a 
reply to people's speculations. 
  Chen Yun, who also passed the Spring Festival and made a 
public appearance in Shanghai as Deng did, is still in Shanghai. 

</TEXT>

