<H3> <TI>   Books on Deng's Thought on SEZ's Published </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2102094694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 2144 
GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2102094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 20 Feb (XINHUA) -- Recently, the Central 
Literature Publishing House and the Social Sciences Literature 
Publishing House, respectively, published Deng Xiaoping 
Thought on and the Practice of Building Special Economic Zones 
[SEZ] [deng xiao ping te qu jian she si xiang yu shi jian 
-- 6772 1420 1627 3676 0575 1696 6080 1835 1927 5280 1395 6432] 
and A Study of Deng Xiaoping Thought on Building Special 
Economic Zones [deng xiao ping te qu jian she si xiang yan 
jiu -- 6772 1420 1627 3676 0575 1696 6080 1835 1927 4282 4496]. 
  Deng Xiaoping Thought on and the Practice of Building 
Special Economic Zones is a collection of materials. The 
book collects Comrade Deng Xiaoping's important propositions 
since 1978 on opening up to the outside world and on building 
SEZ's; propositions on building SEZ's in important party and 
government documents; and economic policies and statutes on 
developing SEZ's promulgated by the National People's Congress, 
the State Council, the governments of coastal provinces and 
cities, and the governments of SEZ's. The book also illustrates 
the profound changes and tremendous achievements of Shenzhen, 
Zhuhai, Shantou, Xiamen, and Hainan since they were built into 
SEZ's. 
  A Study of Deng Xiaoping Thought on Building Special 
Economic Zones is a collection of treatises. It contains 
the latest research findings by workers in theoretical circles, 
as well as those engaged in practical work, over the past two 
years regarding Deng Xiaoping thought on building SEZ's. 
Specifically, the papers compiled by leading cadres, 
specialists, and academics who spent many years assisting in the 
construction of SEZ's illustrate the profound content and 
theoretical significance of Deng Xiaoping thought on building 
SEZ's, expound the great practical effects of the thought, sum 
up the tremendous achievements and valuable experiences in 
building SEZ's over the past 14 years, and outline problems 
arising from the development of SEZ's during the nineties and 
the measures for solving these, all from the perspectives of 
different disciplines -- philosophy, economics, politics, and 
sociology -- and by integrating the past and the present, as 
well as theory and practice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

