<H3> <TI>   Tian Jiyun: `No Way Out Other Than Reform' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2102113994 Hong Kong WEN WEI PO in Chinese 14 Feb 94 p A1 </F>
<F P=103> HK2102113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong WEN WEI PO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dispatch: "Tian Jiyun Visits Peasants in Zhuhai, Stressing </F>
That They Have No Way Out Other Than Reform"] 
  [Text] Zhuhai, 13 Feb (WEN WEI PO) -- On the afternoon of 
the third day of the Spring Festival, several unusual guests 
visited the families of Luo Taoan and Lin Gen, ordinary peasants 
of the village of Guangsheng, in Nanping, Zhuhai. Accompanied 
by Ling Botang, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the 
Guangdong Provincial People's Congress and Liang Guangda and 
other Zhuhai leaders, Tian Jiyun, member of the Political Bureau 
of the CPC Central Committee and vice chairman of the NPC 
Standing Committee, visited the families of these two peasants 
and had cordial discussions with them. 
  It was raining that afternoon. NPC Vice Chairman Tian Jiyun 
first came to Luo Taoan's house. After listening to an 
introduction, he said: Over the past few years, whenever I have 
come to the coastal regions, I have had to go and have a look at 
the rural areas. I am very delighted in my heart to see that 
the peasants are leading a better and better life every day. 
This shows that the path of reform and opening up designed by 
Comrade Deng Xiaoping is completely correct. It is impossible 
to have a prosperous and strong country without developing the 
economy. Facts show that reform and opening up must not be 
shaken. There is no way out other than reform. After this, NPC 
Vice Chairman Tian Jiyun visited the family of Lin Gen, who is a 
fruit grower by occupation. 

</TEXT>

