<H3> <TI>   New Stamps To Honor Non-Communist Patriots </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202044394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0231 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2202044394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, February 22 (XINHUA) -- The Ministry of 
Posts and Telecommunications will issue a new set of stamps to 
honor four noted Chinese non-communist patriots February 25. 
  It will be the second set of stamps commemorating the 
contributions by non-communist patriots for China's liberation 
and socialist construction. 
  The four patriots are Chen Qiyou, former chairman of the 
China Zhi Gong Party (Public Interest Party), Chen Shutong, 
former chairman of the All-China Federation of Industry and 
Commerce, Ma Xulun, former chairman of the Central Committee of 
the China Association for the Promotion of Democracy and former 
vice-chairman of the China Democratic League, and Xu Deheng, 
former chairman of the Jiu San Society's Central Committee. 
  The face values of the stamps will be 0.2 yuan, 0.2 yuan, 
0.5 
yuan and 0.5 yuan. 
  The stamps were designed by Zhu Zhengeng, associate 
professor 
of the Department of Fine Arts of the Central China Teachers 
University. 

</TEXT>

