<H3> <TI>   People's Liberation Army Commends Military Trainers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1802144694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0942 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1802144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Reporter Gai Yumin 5556 3768 3787] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 17 Feb (XINHUA) -- The People's Liberation 
Army's General Staff Department held a meeting today to commend 
301 outstanding trainers of "four military skills" for militia 
units and 49 outstanding trainers of "four military skills" for 
reservist units. 
  China's militia units and the Army's reservist units have 
been stepping up training of a contingent of trainersin recent 
years, thus bringing about a rise in training quality and the 
emergence of a large number of trainers of "four military 
skills." The commended outstanding "four military skills" 
trainers are the advanced representatives from the nation's 
militia and reservist units. They have a strong sense of 
devotion to the revolutioanry cause and to building up a reserve 
force for the national defense. They have a good ideological 
and workstyle; they study hard to improve their professional and 
teaching skills; and they have made positive contributions to do 
a good job in training militiamen and reservists. 

</TEXT>

